readme.feedback: This project was super fun to build. I watched an MIT lecture to get a general understand of Skip lists and read some papers to solidfy the content. I also thought the application problem was fun. I've never been to New York, but I hear the NYC subway system is somewhat challenging to navigate. Coming up with an ideal path to get from point A to point B was super fun and dare I say practical. I enjoyed working on this project as my curiousity grew as I learned more. Thank you for the super fun semester filled with valuable information both practical and interesting.
readme.time: 20 (including research, understanding, conceptualizing, debugging, building test cases, etc.)
